All the typical trigger warnings apply here, so if that is something you cannot handle, no worries. Your mental health is important, so please take care of yourselves as needed.

https://www.youtube.com/@thecultbarshow

JOIN US.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 19 - Dancing for the Devil
episodes.description:
In this volume of The Cult Bar, we discuss the docuseries Dancing for the Devil: The 7M TikTok Cult. This is an interesting one, since we've never had a cult so centered on a social media platform as this one. The cult was established by Robert Shinn, a pastor, and takes advantage of young dancers who are focused on both their careers and God. 

Trigger warnings: High control groups, religious control, monetary control.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 18 - Bikram: Yogi, Guru, Predator
episodes.description:
JOIN US for this month's volume of The Cult Bar where we discuss Bikram: Yogi. Guru, Predator. We will follow the rise and comeuppance of Bikram Choudhury, the founder of Bikram Yoga, an intense style of hot yoga that remains popular to this day. 

Trigger warnings for sexual assault, rape, high control groups, spiritual and financial abuse.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 17 - The Secrets of Hillsong
episodes.description: In the volume of The Cult Bar show, we delve into the cult of Hillsong Church, a worldwide evangelical Pentecostal church based out of Australia. This docuseries focuses on Carl Lentz, a young "hip" pastor who opened the branch in NYC and rose to prominence quickly with celebrity parishioners and and many TV appearances before his downfall from an affair and a sexual assault/rape accusation. Several trigger warnings: religious abuse, sexual abuse, financial control, emotional control and abuse, and volunteer abuse.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 16 - Daughters of the Cult
episodes.description:
Since we had technical issues last month, we're coming back to Daughters of the Cult, a docuseries about "The Mormon Manson," Ervil LeBaron, the leader of a violent polygamist cult. 

Trigger warnings abound: violence, murder, sexual assault, food and financial control, high control group, child assault. This one really did have it all, and not in a good way.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 15: We Warned Them - Freedom Village
episodes.description:
In this volume of The Cult Bar, we are fortunate to have Margaret, one of the creators of the podcast We Warned Them, on to discuss their first season in which they expose Freedom Village USA and the Troubled Teen industry.

We'll delve into how she learned about this cult and deciding to make a podcast about it, the depths of the cult itself, and how so many teenagers who are labeled as "troubled" are trafficked and abused. 

Trigger warnings abound: high control groups, mental, sexual, and physical abuse, and human trafficking, to name a few. 

See you all at 9 PM ET/8 PM CT/6 PM PT on Wednesday, February 7th.

JOIN US.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 14 - Love Has Won: The Cult of Mother God
episodes.description:
In this volume of The Cult Bar Show, we are discussing Love Has Won: The Cult of Mother God. This cult revolves around Amy Carlson, AKA Mother God, and her many Father Gods. Ostensibly they are about connection, but this is a prime example of how New Age ideas can go off the rails and even veer into the Alt-Right pipeline. Trigger Warnings for drug and alcohol abuse, high control groups, financial control, sleep control, food control, and mishandling of a corpse. YES, A CORPSE. 

JOIN US.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 13 - Escaping Twin Flames
episodes.description:
In this volume of The Cult Bar Show, we're covering the Netflix docuseries Escaping Twin Flames. Twin Flames Universe (TFU) is a cult that preys upon lonely folks who are looking for love. Trigger warnings galore, as usual: high control group; financial, emotional, and physical control; gender and queer bigotry and control; diet control. This is the first cult we've covered that is in the dating realm, so be prepared for some awfulness from the leaders, Jeff and Shaleia Ayan. Additionally, we will use the Amazon Prime docuseries Desperately Seeking Soulmate for additional information. 

JOIN US.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 12 - Wild Wild Country
episodes.description: In this month's Cult Bar, Volume 12, Renee and Doug discuss the docuseries Wild Wild County, which details the Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh and his followers known as Rajneeshees and their origins in India to their downfall in rural Oregon. Trigger warnings for high control groups, religious control, financial control, and sexual control. This is the docuseries that lead to us starting this show, so it will be an interesting volume, for certain. JOIN US.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 11 - Ministry of Evil
episodes.description:
In Volume 11 of The Cult Bar Show, we talk about Ministry of Evil - The Twisted Cult of Tony Alamo. This one has ALL the culty things: religious control, financial control, isolation, torture, SA, child SA...it's A LOT. Renee and Doug both were floored by the scope and depravity of it. 

Join us as we navigate the cult of Susan and Tony Alamo. But hold on to your seats, folks.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 10 - Kumare
episodes.description: In Volume 10 of The Cult Bar we'll be talking about the documentary Kumare, where a filmmaker pretends to be a guru to see how many people will follow him. It's a fascinating look into how cult-like followings can begin and how easily people can buy in to be a follower for a host of reasons.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Volume 8 - Bad Vegan
episodes.description: In this volume of The Cult Show Bar, Renee and Doug talk about Bad Vegan. In this case, it's not a full blown cult, but more of micro cult. A con man ensnares an up and coming vegan chef into his world of lies, which ultimately ends up with them on the run. Come join us as we try to unravel how this happened.

episodes.title: The Cult Bar Vol. 5
episodes.description: "Tonight on The Cult Bar Show Doug Zeigler and Renee discuss The Source Family, a cult from the late 1960's and still has some devotees to this day. Led by Jim Baker (No, not THAT Jim Baker), a man with a sordid violent past, we delve into journey that led to them to be a cult. Starting off as a sort of hippie commune that evolved out of a vegan restaurant, it didn't take long for it to become a full blown cult, with Baker declaring himself Father Yod, and later Yahowa, and having a concubine of young girls as his wives. Some folks who regularly went to the restaurant that inspired The Source Family include John Lennon, Julie Christie, and Marlon Brando."
